NEXUSRENT STANDARD RENTAL AGREEMENT TERMS (FY 2026)\r\n\r\nThis document defines the standard tenancy and platform terms between the Tenant, Landlord, and EstateIQ NexusRent platform.\r\n\r\n1) RENT PAYMENT CYCLE\r\n1.1 Tenant shall pay monthly rent on or before the 1st day of each calendar month.\r\n1.2 Rent collection shall be processed through NexusRent payment rails only.\r\n1.3 Subject to fraud/compliance checks, collected rent shall be remitted to the Landlord by the 5th day of the month.\r\n\r\n2) SECURITY DEPOSIT\r\n2.1 Tenant shall provide a refundable security deposit equivalent to two (2) months of agreed monthly rent prior to move-in.\r\n2.2 Deposit shall remain in escrow/security hold as per platform policy until exit settlement is completed.\r\n2.3 Deductions from deposit may be made for unpaid rent, utility dues, damages, exit painting, and approved recovery items.\r\n\r\n3) PROPERTY USAGE & DAMAGE\r\n3.1 Tenant shall maintain property in good condition and avoid misuse, structural changes, or unlawful usage.\r\n3.2 Any damage beyond normal wear and tear shall be chargeable to Tenant based on inspection and repair estimate.\r\n3.3 Tampering with fixtures, appliances, access systems, and safety devices is prohibited.\r\n\r\n4) EXIT, HANDOVER & PAINTING\r\n4.1 Tenant must provide notice as per lease term for vacating.\r\n4.2 On move-out, final inspection will be conducted jointly or through verified inspection workflow.\r\n4.3 Painting/refreshing after exit shall be borne by Tenant unless Landlord has waived in writing.\r\n4.4 Final deposit refund (after applicable deductions) is processed as per settlement SLA.\r\n\r\n5) SCAM PREVENTION & COMPLIANCE\r\n5.1 KYC verification is mandatory for Tenant and Landlord.\r\n5.2 Off-platform payments and direct unrecorded transfers are not permitted.\r\n5.3 Fraudulent claims, forged documents, or payment manipulation may lead to account suspension and legal escalation.\r\n5.4 NexusRent reserves right to hold/flag transactions under risk controls.\r\n\r\n6) MAINTENANCE & DISPUTE HANDLING\r\n6.1 Maintenance requests must be raised on platform for SLA tracking.\r\n6.2 Emergency repairs may be prioritized and reconciled in final settlement.\r\n6.3 Disputes are reviewed through ticket workflow and evidence-based resolution.\r\n\r\n7) NEXUSRENT PLATFORM COMMISSION & CHARGES\r\n7.1 Monthly transaction commission: 1% payable by Tenant and 1% payable by Landlord on monthly rent transactions (minimum ₹500 per side per month).\r\n7.2 Lease onboarding/contract execution fee: ₹1,999 + applicable taxes (one-time at lease start).\r\n7.3 Deposit escrow processing fee: 2% of deposit amount (shared equally by default unless contract states otherwise).\r\n7.4 Payment gateway/statutory taxes shall apply as per prevailing law.\r\n\r\n8) LEGAL & GENERAL\r\n8.1 These are standard platform terms and may be supplemented by city-specific or property-specific clauses.\r\n8.2 In case of conflict, signed lease annexures and lawful regulations shall prevail.\r\n8.3 Both parties agree to cooperate for documentation, police verification (if applicable), and lawful tenancy compliance.\r\n\r\n---\r\nPrepared for: EstateIQ NexusRent\r\nVersion: FY 2026 Standard Terms\r\n